Art Basel 2022 :)

Yesterday, I walked in Topanga canyon with a friend (@yoadrienne20) reflecting on the last 9 months and talking about our dreams for 2023.

Today we sold out Rae Isla's Rocks, a 1,000 piece Music NFT collection that will launch the new chapter of my music. 

Life is strange and beautiful. Sometimes it’s hard and exhausting but somehow it always works out.

Huge thanks to collaborators @solarpunq (art), @alabastrophoto (rock pics), @groovygeologist (geology advice), @krisk_nft (1/1 artist) + a tech team that’s not on IG.

You can view + buy pieces from the full collection on @opensea. 🌊 

Love is an understatement.🧡

Forever running towards the new frontier.👇🏼 

The truth is, touring is unattainable for most artists. Between the cost of travel, lack of guarantees, and team needed to successfully market a tour, it’s really hard to get on the road unless you’re already a megastar. I believe building an online community of supporters can change this reality.

Next week I begin a 2-month journey to 8 cities in the US, Canada, and Mexico to speak on panels and perform solo + with the rock solid band.

“Rae Isla's Web3 Tour ✈️🖥️✨ The first ever collectible tour!”

8 cities. 8 unique NFT drops.

Today we “minted” my debut album Another Life (2021) to the blockchain. 

A way of sovereign distribution that allows for permanence.

I wish I knew about this tech and community back in 2021. Releasing music into the ether can feel very isolating (despite the support and successes - ty @rollingstonemx & others 🙏🏽).

Everything happens for a reason and when it’s meant to.

Now these songs are permanently onchain and can never be erased again 🏜️

Seattle — Aug 24 🌈 

Hometown end of summer show at one of my favorite spaces @abbeyarts 

LA based singer songwriter @yoadrienne.a and I are coming to debut a very special show on Aug 24 + announce something massive that’s happened to our careers live on stage!

You know when you meet someone and it’s obvious it’s not the first time you’ve met? ✨ that’s us. 

I can’t wait to be home and share with you. Tickets are still avail in bio! Bring your cousin/friend/2nd date 🎟️

I’m releasing my most vulnerable song to date. Pre save “The Gardener” to hear it first 🌱♥️

#nature #sadsong #ldr #fall #lovesong #heartbreak #folk #folklore

My mom planted these fruit trees at our childhood home 15 years ago and now they explode with apples, pears and peaches at the end of every summer. Visiting there reminds me that when something’s right, nature will work with you to help it grow. 

I’ve always been a gardener — of the earth and in relationships. Gardeners are often drawn to things that can’t care for themselves, we always try to save em, but nature reveals all in the end. 

“The Gardener” is out everywhere soon. Go ahead and pre save it (link in bio)

🎥 @yoadrienne.a

Come end 2023 and begin 2024 the best way I know how. With the rock solid band and all our friends in these two cities I call home. I’m honored to share both nights with one of my fav songwriters @yoadrienne.a. The venues are intimate so get your tickets fast to avoid any disappointment :)

New song The Gardener is out this Friday.
I’m not entirely sure why this one felt hard to let go of (to distribute). Maybe because hearing the song again and again as I edited videos opened up those old wounds. But you know, I make songs to do just that - open us up so we can all better understand ourselves and each other. I can’t wait for you to listen. Link in the bio :)

It’s out! True story of “The Gardener” - I came home from a trip to see a plant of mine had died, it was more than dead, blackened and rotting. I had counted on someone to care for it. To care for us. If you’ve ever felt like you’re the gardener in a relationship, afraid that if you stop giving it will die, then you’ll know why I wrote this song. Love is simple and when it works, things thrive. I hope you hear your own story in The Gardener, streaming on all platforms 🌱

✨ Almot every time I go through airport security a TSA agent comments on the amount of rocks I have in my bag. Almost always, someone chimes in and says they collect rocks too! Then we swap stories about what collecting means to us and how meaningful the rocks are in remembering our lives and experiences. Today, a man said his wife and him are making a gravel driveway on their farm entirely from rocks made from their “semi retirement” travels. I live for these exchanges, especially with the constant travel this career demands it’s nice to have moments of simple humanity. Funny enough because of my rocks, airport security is now something I look forward to! 🫶🏼🪨

This sweet moments happen to me so often, involving music, rocks, travel, and human connection. I’ll be sharing them more in the subscriber only section of IG.

Can’t think of a more iconic love story 🌱♥️ “The Gardener” now streaming everywhere
